## Form submission with field-level errors

Backends may return `data: { fields: Record<string, string> }` for
`VALIDATION_ERROR`. Surface those next to the inputs.

```tsx
const [fieldErrors, setFieldErrors] = useState<Record<string, string>>({});

try {
  await callApi('/submit-form', formData);
} catch (err) {
  if (err instanceof ApiError && err.code === ErrorCode.VALIDATION_ERROR) {
    const fields = (err.data as { fields?: Record<string, string> } | null)?.fields;
    if (fields) {
      setFieldErrors(fields);
      return;
    }
  }
  setError(
    err instanceof ApiError
      ? (ErrorMessages[err.code] ?? ErrorMessages[ErrorCode.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR])
      : ErrorMessages[ErrorCode.NETWORK_ERROR],
  );
}

// Render
{fieldErrors.email && (
  <p className="text-sm text-destructive">{fieldErrors.email}</p>
)}
```

