## Common mistakes

```typescript
// ❌ Hook called inside an event handler
const handleAction = async () => {
  const t = useTranslations('errors'); // 🚫 Rules of Hooks violation
};

// ❌ Loading not reset on error
setIsLoading(true);
try { await callApi(...); }
catch { /* missing finally */ }

// ❌ Treating `code !== 0` as success (using raw fetch)
const data = await response.json();
setData(data.data); // ignores `data.code`

// ❌ Showing the backend message verbatim
toast.error(err.message);

// ❌ Magic numbers in switch cases
switch (err.code) {
  case 2001: ...   // use ErrorCode.UNAUTHORIZED
}
```

---

## Checklist

- [ ] Hooks (`useTranslations`, `useRouter`, …) called at the top of the component
- [ ] `isLoading` set before request and reset in `finally`
- [ ] `error` reset before each request
- [ ] Early-return when `isLoading` is already true
- [ ] `callApi` used by default; raw `fetch` only when justified
- [ ] `ApiError` branch handles known `ErrorCode.*` cases
- [ ] Network/unknown errors fall back to `ErrorCode.NETWORK_ERROR`
- [ ] No backend `error.message` shown directly to users
- [ ] Loading uses skeleton/spinner appropriately
- [ ] Interactive controls disabled while pending
- [ ] Magic error code numbers replaced with `ErrorCode.*` enum members
